Kernel Data Structures:

It is a software or hardware of an operating system.
It is a lowest layer of an operating system.
It is a part of an operating system.
Which provide services to all parts of an operating system.
It acts as interface between hardware and processes of a computer.
It loads when operating system loads, and remains in the memory until
 Operating system shutdown.

Functions:

1.Task Management
2.Memory Management
3.Device Management 
